<br>
Then I recommend making your own tools to use and put the ones you started with in your Safety Deposit at your bank. If you are not sure on using banks check the Banking Guide for help on that.<br>
<br>
So start finding Metal and Minerals. You will at the minimum want to make the following right off the bat. This will also get your crafting skill going a little bit as well as your survey skill to get the metals and minerals.<br>
<br>
Open your Mineral Survey tool using your new hotkey. You will be asked to set the range since you are a newb Surveyer you will only get one choice of 64 meters and that is fine this will grow as you become better at surveying.<br>
<br>
Scroll down and find Copper Aluminum or Steel. Now start surveying to find one of these that is a high concentration. 70% or better is recomended. Once you find a good resource then start collecting it by hitting your Sample button. Now is time to have a smoke or whatever so you can get some resources saved up.<br>
<br>
Luckily I found a source of Edero a Ferrous Metal Steel at 84% concentration right where I started ) Now start to sample and get a good amount of Metal. You will want to collect at least a few hundred.<br>
<br>
This sampling is where your Surveying Experience comes from. This will get you up the Surveying line in Artisan.<br>
<br>
After getting around 100 or so in Metal I start making my Chemical Survey tool so I can also sample Chemicals. I will need them to make my own Crafting tool. I just like to use my own tools instead of the ones given at start. This also will get some Crafting Experience equiping myself.<br>
<br>
Within about 15 minutes of sampling you should now qualify for Surveying I. Ask around for training or save the cash and pay for training from the Artisan trainer. Remeber though to be a master you must be able to teach. Players need to train other players in order to master a profession. So PCs are normally willing to train you for cheap, much much cheaper than a NPC will charge for training.<br>
<br>
Eventually you will run out of Action which is your green bar. When this happens it is time to rest a few minutes before sampling some more. This is a good time to write down the location of your resource if you found a good one and start crafting your own tools. <br>
<br>
Make a Chemical Survey Device:<br>
<br>
Assembly Enclosure - 8 units of Metal<br>
Controller Mechanism - 8 units of Metal<br>
Scanner Assembly - 3 units of metal<br>
Storage Unit - 8 units of mineral<br>
<br>
I used 27 of the Steel I sampled to make my Chemical Device.<br>
<br>
Once your Action bar is full again start sampling again you need more metal.<br>
<br>
By the time you have fully equiped yourself with all the Survey tools you can make and you will need them all and also your own crafting tool you will qualify for your first block in Engineering, Domestic Arts or Business and you should qualify for Surveying I.<br>
<br>
You should now be on your way to being a productive Artisan. I will post more as time and information permits.<br>
<br>
